        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> No offense guys, but you make me laugh.  Tyrial, you just sat there and admitted you were able to beat your rogue friend once despite his uber gear and AA.  I have a few comments to reply in our little debate that I am very much enjoying.</P><P>1st - If you want to enter the "AA" realm, well that's a whole new ball game isn't it?  I am specing my AA points rather nicely myself.  Do I have dire charm yet?  No, but I would love it.  I wasn't talking about the best of the best rogue vs necro duel lol.  Don't forget the abilites YOU will have with some well place AA.  For instance, casting deftness and channeling focus.  Suddenly I can cast those lengthy spells within a proper amount of time for my duel, such as funeral pyre and my 720 point lifetap.  So a rogue has 4k+ hps??  So do warriors.  Chaotic Backstab? LOL  Yeah that would suck, but then at that AA level I get to use lifeburn, fight is over.  Come on, what you are saying is "I dunno, if Mike Tyson takes on that 12 year old kid over there he's gonna win."  Yeah, if I'm a normal necro with no AA fighting an AA uber rogue, the fight will be a bit tough ;).</P><P>2nd - I refuse to argue any more about this silly cancel magic subject until you all agree to actually try it.  Like I said, I have tried it on many subjects 2 boxing.  AGAIN, melees dont have "good" cancel magic spells.  PUMICE STONE??? lol what a joke.  Sounds like eq logic 2 years ago, those are so nerfed it's not even funny.  The cast time is ridiculous for a chance to cancel a mere one buff.  And AGAIN, half the time they cancel their own silly buffs, like those nice right clicky ones from cobalt items that are lower level spells.</P><P>You guys talk like people who don't practice :P  That's all I have to say.  Do I lose?  hell yeah, I didn't say I never lost lol.  I just know that because I actually practice the stuff and not just talk about it, I win a lot more.  I appreciate the power our class has.</P><P>3rd - Arena close quarters fight.  Yep, that would be hard.  I don't have a good answer for that.  I know that I duel a lot in the traditional arena off Lake Rathe.  I can say that I don't care if shadowstep is unreliable, I cast it again in under 1 sec and it virtually takes no mana.  If you really want to stir them up, cast it 3 times in a row until you are in the place you want to be :P lol.</P><P><BR>Ok, to day my most difficult duel was with AA pally, had run3, perma see invis so no right clicky prenurf COS for me, and he could heal the piss out of himself.  Luckily we dueled in EC and I could restore my health off some poor vitimized snakes outside haha.  The duel ended in basically a stalemate.  Neither of us could kill eachother.  I don't have the AAs I want yet though ;).</P><P>Be safe brothers,</P><P>Doleo<BR>60th Warlock of the Rathe.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
